name: Ingrid Andress
summary: Country music star Ingrid Andress' performance of the national anthem at the 2024 Home Run Derby has sparked widespread criticism online. Critics have slammed the performance as "one of the worst" renditions, with some describing it as "rocky" and "terrible." Many have found the performance unconventional, likening it to "singing in cursive" or "spoken word." The backlash has even extended to the MLB player Alec Bohm, who was seen struggling to maintain a straight face during the performance. Despite the negative reception, some viewers have defended Andress, arguing that her unique interpretation has united Americans.

name: Glenn Youngkin
summary: There have been significant developments in Virginia's education system and political landscape. Governor Glenn Youngkin has implemented an executive order to restrict cell phone usage in K-12 schools. This decision has sparked discussion about the potential benefits and drawbacks of limiting phone access in schools. Furthermore, speculation has emerged regarding Youngkin's possible consideration as Donald Trump's running mate in a potential 2024 presidential election. Youngkin has delivered a speech at the Republican National Convention, further fueling discussions about his political aspirations. Despite rumors, Youngkin has dismissed the possibility of a vice presidential run, expressing contentment with his current role as Virginia's governor. His recent actions, including ordering flags to be flown at half-staff in honor of a victim at a Trump rally, have drawn attention to his support for the former president.

name: Derecho
summary: Midwestern and Northeastern regions experienced severe weather events, including a derecho that caused significant damage across nearly 500 miles in Chicago and the Midwest. A derecho is a widespread, long-lived windstorm that can cause substantial damage. In Iowa, a combination of tornadoes and large hail impacted the state. The Midwest and Northeast remain at risk for severe thunderstorms, while efforts continue in Houston to repair damage from a previous derecho. Meanwhile, officials are assessing whether the recent storms in Iowa meet the criteria for a derecho designation. Grants are available to assist Iowa towns in replanting trees lost during the 2020 derecho.
